Summary​

- Included a library to enable IR remote functionality.​

- Assigned descriptive variable names to Arduino digital pins for clearer, more readable code.​

- Mapped variables to specific IR remote signals for each button press.​

- Used variable definitions to improve code clarity and understanding.​

- Created global structures and initialized global variables for consistent program-wide access.​

- Wrote helper functions to simplify the creation and readability of later functions.​

- Developed motor-control functions to operate individual motors.​

- Built higher-level movement functions that coordinate both motors to control the car’s motion.​

- Implemented functions to control LED headlights and turn-signal behavior.
